|stock_os=Linux;2.6.22; |tp_firmware=FreshTomato, [http://www.linksysinfo.org/index.php?threads/new-tomato-firmware-for-d-link-dir-865l-ac1750-router.70230/ vineyard's custom Tomato version] |802dot11_protocols=abgn+ac |default_ssid=dlink-XXXX, dlink-media-XXXX |default_ssid_regex=^dlink-[A-F0-9]{4}$,,, ^dlink-media-[A-F0-9]{4}$ |default_ip=192.168.0.1 |default_user=admin |oui=90:94:E4 |oui_eth=90:94:E4 }} {{TagLine|Wireless AC1750 Dual Band Cloud Router}} :{{ProductPage|http://www.dlink.com/us/en/home-solutions/connect/routers/dir-865l-cloud-router-5700}} {{SupportPage|vendor=D-Link|model=DIR-865L}} "8WRGAC01.2A1G" is silkscreened on the back of the main board. :The main board is using ''TAICON'' electrolytic capacitors. "8WMCAC01.2A1G" is silkscreened on the 802.11ac wireless module in the FCC photos. The default SSID patterns for the device are '''dlink-XXXX''' and '''dlink-media-XXXX'''. '''XXXX''' :is the last two octets of the respective wireless interface's MAC address (upper case letters). The power adapter shown in the FCC photos (and presumably the one included with the device) :is an '''Asian Power Devices''' WA-36C12R (100-240VAC ~ 50-60Hz, 1A Max. -> 12VDC, 3A). {{WiFiCert|WFA15518|07/20/2012}} ===Serial=== The default telnet credentials are '''Alphanetworks''' (user) :and ''wrgac01_dlob.hans_dir865'' (password). ====Pinout==== The pinout seems to be the standard current '''Alpha''' pinout.
